Package ca.corefacility.gview.style.datastyle

Provides for storage/manipulation of style information specific to the particular data we are displaying (such as the specific sequence/features).

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    FeatureContainerStyle
    This allows for (data) styles that contain features, such as sets and slots, to interface more easily.
    StyleHolder
    Describes a type which can hold sets of item styles (sets of ItemHolderStyles).
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    DataStyle
    DataStyle controls any style information directly related to the specific genome data to use.
    FeatureHolderStyle
    Stores the style information for a particular set of features.
    FeatureHolderStyleFactory
    Used to assign unique id's to each featureHolderStyle.
    LabelStyle
    Defines style information dealing with labels of features.
    PlotBuilderType
    Used to generate a specific type of plot builder
    PlotBuilderType.Annotation  
    PlotBuilderType.GCContent  
    PlotBuilderType.GCSkew  
    PlotBuilderType.Points  
    PlotBuilderType.Range  
    PlotDrawerType  
    PlotDrawerType.Bar  
    PlotDrawerType.Center  
    PlotDrawerType.Line  
    PlotDrawerType.Solid  
    PlotStyle  
    SlotItemStyle
    Stores style information specific to a set of items on the map (may or may not be features).
    SlotStyle
    Defines a class for the style information for a particular slot.
